<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="11" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="11">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="11">
Proposed IUCN Red List Category 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="11">Endangered</emphasis>
(EN): B2a, B2b (
<normalizedToken originalValue="i–iii">i-iii</normalizedToken>
): B2: total area of occupancy less than 5000 km2 (ca. 904 km2). B1a, severely fragmented; B1b (
<normalizedToken originalValue="i–iii">i-iii</normalizedToken>
), habitat continuing decline inferred. The suitable habitat for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lorence &amp; W. L. Wagner" authorityYear="2011" class="Pteridopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Dryopteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Filicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="11" phylum="Polypodiophyta" rank="species" species="macropholis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="11">Dryopteris macropholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Nuku Hiva (ca. 340 km2), Ua Huka (ca. 83 km2), Ua Pou (ca. 105 km2), Hiva Oa (ca. 315 km2), and Tahuata (ca. 61 km2) is restricted to mountain slopes and summits, indicated as an endangered environment that is threatened by human activity (deforestation and fire), feral animals, and invasive plants, reducing the extent of the forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
